articles.author: Caroline Linton
articles.title: 3 U.S. Marines killed in Osprey aircraft crash in Australia - CBS News
articles.description: The Osprey aircraft, which was conducting a training exercise, was carrying 23 personnel, the U.S. Marines said.
articles.content:
At least three U.S. Marines were killed Sunday when an Osprey aircraft carrying 23 personnel crashed on a north Australian island during a training exercise, U.S. military officials said.
